gomodel:SYNGO_5088  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 2c: Adult mouse hippocampal sections were singly stained with rabbit polyclonal anti-l-afadin, followed by immunoelectron microscopy with the silver-enhanced immunogold method. Afadin (AFDN) was detected on both the pre- and post-synaptic plasma membrane facing the synaptic cleft.\n\"It is therefore likely that at puncta adherentia junctions of these synapses, nectin-1 and -3 form a hetero-trans-dimer that is associated with l-afadin on both sides of the junctions.\"\n\nFigure 4b: a similar localization was observed in developing mouse hippocampal sections on P4, P7, and P14.. Experimental description: Results, Figure 2 legend: \"Adult mouse hippocampal sections were singly stained with the rabbit polyclonal anti-nectin-1, rabbit polyclonal anti-nectin-3, or rabbit polyclonal anti-l-afadin Ab,\"\n\nantibody:\n\"A rabbit polyclonal anti-l-afadin Ab, which specifically recognizes l-afadin, but not s-afadin, was made as described by Mandai et al. (1997).\" PMID:9334353" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-24" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5088" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

